20/05/2008
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Hospital administrator Sorin Oprescu, an independent candidate formerly with the Social Democrat Party is on track to win 39% of the vote in the upcoming mayor elections in Bucharest, according to the latest survey by Insomar, a local pollster.
Romania's local elections are scheduled to take place on June 1st, with a run-off on June 15th, if necessary.
Vasile Blaga, of the Democratic Liberal Party, is second with 24% of the vote, while Ludovic Orban, of the National Liberal Party, is third with 12%.
(Realitatea TV - 19/05/08)
